@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>
    "Employee Portal Privacy Policy

    At [Company Name], we are committed to protecting the privacy of our employees. This privacy policy applies to the employee portal and outlines how we collect, use, and protect personal information that is provided to us through the portal.

    Information We Collect

    We collect personal information from our employees when they access and use the employee portal. This information may include, but is not limited to, name, employee ID, job title, department, contact information, and login credentials.

    We may also collect additional information, such as performance evaluations, training records, and benefits information, as necessary to manage employee records and administer company policies.

    Use of Information

    The information collected through the employee portal is used to manage employee records, administer company policies, and communicate with employees about important information related to their employment.

    Protection of Information

    We take the protection of personal information very seriously. Access to personal information is restricted to authorized personnel only and all data is stored on secure servers. We also regularly review and update our security measures to ensure that employee information is protected.

    Employees are responsible for keeping their login credentials secure and should not share their login information with others. If an employee suspects any unauthorized access to their account, they should immediately notify their supervisor and the IT department.

    Changes to this Policy

    We reserve the right to make changes to this privacy policy at any time. Any changes will be communicated to employees through the employee portal."
</p>
